    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1862-04-02T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1862-04-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="492" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d492">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Pike</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 48.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1862-04-02">
                            <hi rend="italic">April</hi> 2, 1862</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> Your despatch of March 12 (No. 41) has
                            been received. Your account of the system of finance and revenue
                            existing in the Netherlands is very interesting. In the belief that it
                            may prove useful in the present emergency, I shall take pleasure in
                            procuring its submission to Congress.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">James S. Pike</hi>, Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c, &amp;c, &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
